commit.message:
choose returns `nil` when no values are given

It was returning randomly 0 or 1 before changin the `range` method and failing
afterwards.
Add thanks in CHANGELOG

Refactor and fix range method

Use rand with range to avoid having two cases. This also fix the fact that
invalid ranges (for example `(0..-1)`) where inversing the range and returning
a number. Now invalid ranges return `nil` instead.

Remove LOGO118OC

It is already in the `logo` folder.
